{"id":"wages","term":"Wages","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Rate of (mention only in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 20:2\">Matt. 20:2</a>); to be punctually paid (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 19:13\">Lev. 19:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 24:14\">Deut. 24:14</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 24:15\">15</a>); judgements threatened against the withholding of (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 22:13\">Jer. 22:13</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Malachi 3:5\">Mal. 3:5</a>; comp. <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"James 5:4\">James 5:4</a>); paid in money (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 20:1\">Matt. 20:1-14</a>); to Jacob in kind (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 29:15\">Gen. 29:15</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:20\">20</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 30:28\">30:28</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 31:7\">31:7</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 31:8\">8</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 31:41\">41</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Matthew 20:2","Leviticus 19:13","Deuteronomy 24:14","Deuteronomy 24:15","Jeremiah 22:13","Malachi 3:5","James 5:4","Matthew 20:1","Genesis 29:15","Genesis 1:20","Genesis 30:28","Genesis 31:7","Genesis 31:8","Genesis 31:41"]}